{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 118, "line_start": 118, "page_hint": null, "section": "Introduction", "text": "Three types of cyclic loading were considered, including (1) cycling of specimens, which were preloaded in compression, between zero and a constant stress level less than the preload stress value, (2) cycling in compression wherein the"}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 146, "line_start": 146, "page_hint": null, "section": "Synopsis of Reported Results*", "text": "The slopes of the stress-strain curves at the origin for continued loading (type 1) were the same order of magnitude as given by sonic measurements."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 146, "line_start": 146, "page_hint": null, "section": "Synopsis of Reported Results*", "text": "Seldin<sup>4</sup> also found good comparisons between sonic moduli and the slopes at zero stress as measured from tensile and compressive stress-strain curves for several grades of molded graphite."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 148, "line_start": 148, "page_hint": null, "section": "Synopsis of Reported Results*", "text": "Arragon and Berthier found that cyclic compressive tests of type 2 cause the apparent density to increase."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 150, "line_start": 150, "page_hint": null, "section": "Synopsis of Reported Results*", "text": "A schematic diagram, which depicts the essential features of the behavior observed from a test of type 2, is shown in Fig."}
{"claim_type": "figure-reference", "line_end": 150, "line_start": 150, "page_hint": null, "section": "Synopsis of Reported Results*", "text": "Arragon and Berthier<sup>3</sup> also discovered that straight lines drawn through the unloading point and the point of zero stress for each cycle converge at a single point as shown in the figure."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 154, "line_start": 154, "page_hint": null, "section": "Synopsis of Reported Results*", "text": "In the case of test type 3, which was used in the study by Arragon and Berthier, $^{3}$ each specimen was subjected to 12 cycles."}
{"claim_type": "figure-reference", "line_end": 167, "line_start": 167, "page_hint": null, "section": "Ornl Dwg. 67-2981", "text": "Figure 8, which shows the strain ratios for EGCR-type AGOT graphite as functions of longitudinal strain,[2] provides a clear illustration."}
{"claim_type": "figure-reference", "line_end": 167, "line_start": 167, "page_hint": null, "section": "Ornl Dwg. 67-2981", "text": "In this figure, the subscript 3 refers to the parallel, or with-grain direction, while the subscripts 1 and 2 refer to two orthogonal (across-grain) directions in the plane of isotropy."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 173, "line_start": 173, "page_hint": null, "section": "Ornl Dwg. 67-2981", "text": "Cyclic Stress-Strain Curves for a With-Grain EGCR-Type AGOT Specimen (12 Cycles)."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 176, "line_start": 176, "page_hint": null, "section": "Ornl Dwg. 67-2981", "text": "Cyclic Stress-Strain Curves for a With-Grain RVD Specimen (5 Cycles)."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 202, "line_start": 202, "page_hint": null, "section": "Additional Investigations", "text": "The 0.l00-in.-diam longitudinal hole was bored in each specimen to allow for making permeability measurements, and a smooth machine finish was used, without grinding or polishing."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 204, "line_start": 204, "page_hint": null, "section": "Additional Investigations", "text": "Each specimen was marked for gage location using a HB grade drafting pencil to avoid scratching the surface and to provide indications that would not be removed by heat treating the specimen at $3000^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}$ (to be discussed later)."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 204, "line_start": 204, "page_hint": null, "section": "Additional Investigations", "text": "Budd Metalfilm, type C6-121-A, strain gages with a 0.125-in. gage length were used."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 206, "line_start": 206, "page_hint": null, "section": "Additional Investigations", "text": "Tensile tests were performed using steel clam-shell fixtures attached to the ends and 0.20-in.-diam, stainless steel, stranded-wire cables for transmitting the load to the specimen."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 208, "line_start": 208, "page_hint": null, "section": "Additional Investigations", "text": "For those cases in which the specimens were heat treated, a 100 kw, 3000 Hertz induction furnace was used for this purpose."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 208, "line_start": 208, "page_hint": null, "section": "Additional Investigations", "text": "The inside dimensions were a diameter of 9 in. and a length of 14 in., and the specimens were heated in Argon at atmospheric pressure."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 208, "line_start": 208, "page_hint": null, "section": "Additional Investigations", "text": "The time to reach the $3000^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}$ temperature level was 45 minutes."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 208, "line_start": 208, "page_hint": null, "section": "Additional Investigations", "text": "The furnace was cooled from 3000 to"}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 223, "line_start": 223, "page_hint": null, "section": "Photo 76468", "text": "2500°C in approximately 15 minutes, from 2500 to 2000°C in about 1 hour, and from 2000°C to room temperature in 12 to 14 hours."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 225, "line_start": 225, "page_hint": null, "section": "Photo 76468", "text": "It was then cycled ten times between zero and a stress, $\\sigma_{0}$ , which was in the range given by"}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 261, "line_start": 261, "page_hint": null, "section": "Ornl Dwg. 69-8209", "text": "16 and 17 show the results for sets of across-grain specimens."}
